{"questionId":"10987","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub>, reacts with oxygen in welding torches.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Write an equation for the complete combustion of ethyne.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub> (g) + 2.5O<sub>2</sub> (g) → 2CO<sub>2</sub> (g) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l)<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>2C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub> (g) + 5O<sub>2</sub> (g) → 4CO<sub>2</sub> (g) + 2H<sub>2</sub>O (l)&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10987","referenceCode":"19M.2.sl.TZ2.1a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Write an equation for the complete combustion of ethyne.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}